$0: UNIVERSAL GLOSSARY

# -- $0: UNIVERSAL GLOSSARY --
# Sigil | Name | Type | Risk | Cognitive Layer | Description
# IDN   | identity   | attrs      | B | Semantic       | Skill identity
# DOM   | domain     | attrs      | B | Semantic       | Adoption scope and context
# AXM   | axiom      | cuerpo     | H | Prefrontal     | Non-negotiable principle
# CNST  | constraint | attrs      | H | Prefrontal     | Hard operational boundary
# KNW   | knowledge  | attrs      | B | Semantic       | Protocol knowledge
# HDL   | handler    | attrs-pos  | M | Semantic       | Operation descriptor (positional)
# STAT  | status     | attrs      | B | Semantic       | Status or maturity declaration
# DIAG  | diagram    | bloque     | M | Episodic/Visual | Normative diagram
# REF   | reference  | attrs      | B | Semantic       | Source or cross-reference
# RSK   | risk       | attrs      | M | Prefrontal     | Protocol risk and mitigation
# AUD   | audit      | attrs      | M | Prefrontal     | Spec audit record
# !     | rule       | attrs      | H | Prefrontal     | Mandatory compact rule
#
# Types:
# attrs = key:value pairs
# attrs-pos = positional with explicit contract
# cuerpo = free text body
# bloque = verbatim multiline block
#
# Positional contracts:
# contract: HDL | operation | status | requires

$1: IDENTITY

IDN:skill{name:"codec-cortex", version:"1.0.0", status:"specification", nature:"cognitive_memory_protocol"}
DOM:protocol{area:"LLM/SLM contextual memory", format:".cortex", memory_output:"HCORTEX", conversational_output:"CORTEX-OUT"}

$2: AXIOMS

AXM:level_separation{
SKILL.cortex governs behavior and contracts. It never stores live working state.
}
AXM:self_contained{
Every .cortex artifact must include a minimal $0 local glossary for safe interpretation.
}

$3: CONSTRAINTS

CNST:no_live_state_in_skill{rule:"SKILL.cortex MUST NOT contain FCS/OBJ/WRK/STP/NXT as live state.", severity:"blocking", survive:"min"}

$4: HANDLERS

HDL:decode{decode | current | ".cortex file"}
HDL:encode{encode | planned | "AST + glossary"}
HDL:verify{verify | planned | "AST + AST comparator"}
